Turkey Car Loan Rates Surge After Non-Repayments, Haberturk Says

-- B y   M a r k   B e n t l e y
-- 
2011-04-25T05:56:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/turkey-car-loan-rates-surge-after-non-repayments-haberturk-says.html
Turkish banks have raised interest
rates on loans for cheaper cars to as much as 1.44 percent
monthly to cover the cost of previous non-repayments, Haberturk
reported.  Rates on loans for luxury cars remain as low as 0.81
percent monthly, the newspaper said citing unidentified bankers
and analysts.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
